name: phik
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "PhiK" %}
{% set version = "0.12.2" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://github.com/KaveIO/{{ name }}/archive/v{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 5810fbe9dd87441fe404a67aa550e2c4c88c4deec834083bc2ff85756296a3ba

build:
  number: 0
  entry_points:
    - phik_trial = phik.entry_points:phik_trial  # [win]
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('cxx') }}
    - cmake >=3.16
    - ninja  # [not win]
    - make  # [linux]
  host:
    - python
    - pip
    - setuptools >=42
    - pybind11 >=2.8.1
    - pybind11-abi
    - pybind11-stubgen
    - scikit-build >=0.13.1
  run:
    - python
    - numpy >=1.18.0
    - scipy >=1.5.2
    - pandas >=0.25.1
    - matplotlib-base >=2.2.3
    - joblib >=0.14.1


test:
  imports:
    - phik

about:
  home: https://github.com/KaveIO/PhiK
  license: Apache-2.0
  license_family: Apache
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: Phi_K correlation analyzer library
  description: |
    Phi_K is a new and practical correlation coefficient based on several
    refinements to Pearson's hypothesis test of independence of two variables.
  doc_url: http://phik.readthedocs.io/
  dev_url: https://github.com/KaveIO/PhiK

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - philip-khor
